<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, August 27 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Shaul Mofaz, Chief of General Staff of the Israel
Defense Force (IDF), appointed a committee Sunday to investigate a
overnight shootout with Palestinian militant group in the West
Bank.
</P>
<P>
Three IDF soldiers were killed in the clash with "Palestinian
terrorists" near Nablus Saturday night and a fourth one was
injured, apparently by "friendly fire," the IDF spokesman's office
said Sunday morning. (Israel-Shootout-Investigation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Two bombs exploded in Medan, capital of Indonesia's
North Sumatra, on Sunday, wounding two people and damaging
buildings, according to the Antara News Agency.
</P>
<P>
"They were home-made bombs, and it seems that they were using
the same materials used in the bomb which exploded in a Protestant
church in May," Medan chief police senior superintendent Hasyim
Irianto said.
</P>
<P>
The first bomb exploded at 02:20 a.m. (1920 GMT Saturday) in
front of a small car repair shop in the southern part of Medan.
Five minutes later and about seven meters away, a second bomb
exploded in front of a priest's house. (Indonesia-Bombs)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MANILA -- The Abu Sayyaf Sunday afternoon released five foreign
hostages including four seized from Malaysia and kept them captive
for more than four months in its jungle lair in the southern
Philippine island of Jolo.
</P>
<P>
The freed four women and one man arrived by helicopter at the
Edwin Andrews air base in Zamboanga, a port city near Jolo, at
around 6 p.m., under the escort of Philippine government chief
negotiator Robert Aventajado and Libyan envoy Rajab Azzarouq, the
ABS-CBN TV station reported. (Philippines-Hostage Release)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Six people were killed and 16 others injured Sunday
when a passenger ship collided with an empty barge in the Russia's
central Perm region, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Voskhod-42 collided with the barge in Votkinskoye storage
lake amid thick fog, Interfax said, quoting the Russian Ministry
of Emergency Situations. (Russia-Ship-Collision)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
DHAKA -- At least 20 people were killed and scores injured in
Bangladesh Sunday in two separate incidents, one fire incident in
a garment factory and the other a roof collapse, police and fire
brigade sources said. (Bangladesh-Incidents)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ARTA, Djibouti -- Somali President Abdiqasim Salad Hassan,
elected by the Somali transitional parliament, was sworn in on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Salad became the first head of state in Somalia since the Horn
of Africa country fell into anarchy in 1991. He will implement his
duty under the transitional parliament which will last for three
years from now on. (Somalia-President)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak said Sunday that
in terms of the negotiations with the Palestinians, the ball is
now in Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat's court.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at Sunday morning's weekly cabinet meeting, Barak
stressed that it should be the Palestinians who will decide
whether or not to move toward a peace deal, according to a
statement issued by his office. (Israel-Palestine-Negotiation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Voters in central and northern Lebanon began to cast
ballots Sunday in the first round of voting on a new parliament.
</P>
<P>
This is the third parliamentary elections since the end of the
1975-1990 civil war. (Lebanon-Parliamentary Elections)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkish coast guards have recovered eight bodies from
a capsized Turkish boat that sank Saturday night in the Aegean Sea,
Anatolia News Agency reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The boat, setting out from Turkish Bodrum township of Mugla
province in Aegean region to Greek Kos Island, was carrying 32
illegal immigrants as it sank off Bodrum shortly after midnight.
</P>
<P>
The coast guards had rescued six people including the Turkish
skipper, but the other 18 are missing. (Turkey-Boat Capsize)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MANILA -- Philippine President Joseph Estrada confirmed Sunday
afternoon that he is softening the government's "all or nothing"
stance on the Sulu hostage crisis following the release of five
foreign hostages by the Abu Sayyaf earlier on the day.
</P>
<P>
Estrada told reporters that appeals from European envoys to
ease the government position in dealing with the Abu Sayyaf rebels
prompted this decision. (Philippines-Hostage-Stance)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MANILA -- Ten civilians were killed Sunday morning by suspected
members of the Moro Islamic Liberation Front in a province in the
southern island of Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
An undetermined number of armed men fired upon a passenger
jeepney loaded with commuters at a place in Carmen town, North
Cotabato Province at around 6 a.m., killing nine people on the
spot, the local ABS-CBN TV station reported.
</P>
<P>
Another one died upon arrival at a nearby hospital, it added. (
Philippines-Killing)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- A fire that broke out earlier Sunday at the world's
second tallest TV tower in Moscow is spreading, but nobody was
hurt.
</P>
<P>
As a result, most television programs and radio broadcast have
been knocked off the air in Moscow.
</P>
<P>
All people have been evacuated from the tower and authorities
are warning about possible malfunctions in communications at the
frequencies used by medical services and the police. (Russia-Fire)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000828.0003 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Wins Cosafa Castle Cup Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe whitewashed Lesotho 3-0
in the second leg of Cosafa Castle Cup soccer final in Bulawayo,
Zimbabwe Sunday and won the cup title with 6-0 on aggregate:
</P>
<P>
Luke Petros of the host team scored the opening goal in the
15th minute and teammates Robson Chisango and Benjamin Mwaruwaru
added one each in the 75th and 78th minutes respectively.
</P>
<P>
About 35,000 spectators watched the match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
