<HEADLINE> S. Leone, UNAMSIL Negotiate Release of Abducted Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The Sierra Leonean government and
the United Nations Mission in Sierra Leone (UNAMSIL) have been
conducting busy negotiations with the rebel group for the safe
return of 12 abducted soldiers, according to a report reaching
here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
UNAMSIL military spokesman Patrick Coker was quoted as saying
in Freetown, capital of Sierra Leone that the UNAMSIL is still
continuing the dialogue with the rebel group for the release of
the soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The soldiers, 11 Britons and one Sierra Leonean, were captured
by the rebel group, known as the West Side Boys, last Friday when
they were patrolling along the Freetown-Masiaka highway.
</P>
<P>
The soldiers are reportedly well treated and currently "in good
conditions", Coker said.
</P>
<P>
However, the spokesman kept his mouth shut tight over the
possibility that the UNAMSIL is prepared to use force if present
negotiations fail to secure the release of the abducted soldiers.
</P>
