<HEADLINE> Pro-Reform Students Attacked in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 28 (Xinhua) -- A group of university students,
belonging to Iran's pro-reform student group -- the Office to
Foster
Unity (OFU), were attacked Monday by a number of assailants in
Borujere, a city in the country's western province of Lorestan.
</P>
<P>
The students were on their way back to Tehran from Khoramabad,
capital of Lorestan, where the OFU had held its seventh annual
conference in the past week.
</P>
<P>
The assailants threw stones and bricks to the buses carrying the
students, with some of them, both male and female, injured in the
attacks, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The police had to intervene in order to put an end to the
attacks, added the report.
</P>
<P>
A local official confirmed the incident and said the attacks
were organized. But he did not mention the identities of the
attackers.
</P>
<P>
The OFU, the country's most influential student group that
supports President Mohammad Khatami's reform programs, held its
annual conference in Khoramabad last week.
</P>
<P>
But the gathering resulted in a series of clashes between
supporters and opponents of the group. A policeman was reportedly
killed in the clashes.
</P>
<P>
The group was forced to call off its meeting on Sunday, two days
before the scheduled date for ending the conference, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
Rallies and demonstrations have become frequent in Iran as the
two major political factions in the country, namely the
conservative establishment and the nascent reformers, escalate
their struggle.
</P>
<P>
The conservatives, who are still in control of many key
government organs, have in recent months stepped up their efforts
to undermine the reformist campaign, which ended the long-time
conservative
domination of the Majlis (parliament) in February's election.
</P>
<P>
So far more than 20 pro-reform papers and journals have been
banned from publishing and a number of reformist figures have been
imprisoned on charges of violating Islamic principles and
advocating American-style reforms.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, conservative radicals often disturb pro-reform allies
and launch violent attacks on pro-reform students and people.
</P>
</TEXT>
