<HEADLINE> EU Releases 11 Million U.S. Dollars to Support Africa's Food Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) has
released an additional 13 million euros (about 11.2 million U.S.
dollars) to support the World Food Program (WFP) operations in
Africa, a statement released here on Monday said.
</P>
<P>
The money will be used to fund WFP projects in various African
countries including Ethiopia, Eritrea, Kenya, Sudan and Tanzania,
which have been hit by drought and a critical shortage of food,
the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Last month, the EU released 90 million euros (about 81 million
dollars) to support WFP operations in Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
