<HEADLINE> French Interior Minister Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AFP quoted government sources as saying Monday afternoon that
the departure of Chevenement from the Jospin cabinet as well as
his replacement will be announced on Tuesday by a communique of
the prime minister's office.
</P>
<P>
As a rule, Chevenemenbt should formally present his resignation
to President Jacques Chirac, but AFP said that Chirac will surely
accept his resignation.
</P>
<P>
The decision for Chevenement's departure was made during his
meeting with Jospin Monday, said AFP.
</P>
<P>
As the head of the Citizens' Movement Party who joined the
leftwing coalition of Jospin three years ago, Chevenement has
openly criticized Jospin's plan to give Corsica more autonomous
power in administration, territorial management and fiscal policy.
</P>
