<DOCNO> XIE20000828.0036 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. Chief Urges to Strengthen U.N. Mission in Sierra Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 28 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan on Monday urged to strengthen the United Nations
Mission in Sierra Leone (UNAMSIL) to 20,500 personnel to help the
government to regain control of the country from rebel forces.
</P>
<P>
In a report to the Security Council, Annan said he believes
that the priority tasks can largely be achieved under the current
U.N. mandate, provided the U.N. mission receives necessary
resources and support from member states.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. chief called for strengthening the force to 20,500,
including 260 military observers, and for extending the mission's
mandate, which expires on September 8, for another six months.
</P>
<P>
Annan said the rebels continue to control large parts of the
country and the threat they pose to government forces, U.N.
peacekeepers and the general population should not be
underestimated.
</P>
<P>
"The rebel Revolutionary United Front (RUF) is believed to have
a strength of several thousands fighters. It is relatively well-
equipped and, in spite of divisions between some groups, maintains
a relatively-well established system of command and control," the
U.N. chief said.
</P>
<P>
The additional troops will enable the United Nations force to
strengthen its presence, first with two infantry battalions
deploying at key locations in eastern and western Sierra Leone,
and then gradually eastward with three additional battalions, he
said.
</P>
<P>
In the future, the U.N. chief said, the force may be required
to deploy to other key areas not under government control,
including the main diamond producing areas.
</P>
<P>
Stressing the mission's peacekeeping role, Annan said "it
should be made clear to all hostile armed groups that UNAMSIL,
while fully committed to its peacekeeping objectives, has the
means and determination to use force when attacked or challenged."
</P>
<P>
He also urged the international community to support the
mission and help promote a political solution in the war-torn
country.
</P>
<P>
RUF rebels reignited Sierra Leone's nine-year civil war in May
by seizing about 500 U.N. peacekeepers which severely embarrassed
the United Nations and prompted a reassessment of the U.N. mission.
UNAMSIL was established in October 1999.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
