<DOCNO> XIE20000828.0038 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chirac Urges Israel, Syria to Resume Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a speech to the conference of French ambassadors posted
overseas, Chirac said that his objective is to help Syrian
President Bashar Assad and Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak
overcome their distrust toward each other and to find the way
toward a just, global and lasting peace.
</P>
<P>
As for the peace process between Israel and Palestinians,
Chirac said that the hope for a peace agreement is always there
despite the failure of the two sides to strike an agreement at
Camp David last month.
</P>
<P>
He said that France and other European Union states are ready
to provide their help to Israel and Palestinians in their final
efforts to reach a peace agreement.
</P>
<P>
He also said that a future Palestinian state should be equipped
with all the conditions for its survival and should be able to
contribute to the security in the region.
</P>
<P>
Chirac also promised that France will continue to support the
Lebanese government in regaining sovereignty over all its
territory and building an independent, unified, democratic and
modern state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
