<HEADLINE> Two Killed in Air Crashes in Switzerland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, August 28 (Xinhua) -- A light aircraft and a helicopter
have crashed in two separate accidents almost simultaneously in
the Alps in eastern Switzerland, killing two people and injuring
three others, according to a Swiss Radio International report
Monday.
</P>
<P>
It is not yet known what caused the crashes, which occurred
within five minutes of each other and only 20 kilometers apart.
</P>
<P>
Police in canton Graubunden said the German-registered aircraft
came down in the Bever valley, on the south side of the Albula
pass, after catching fire.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss air rescue service, Rega, said it received a distress
call at 0901 GMT on Monday morning, but that it was unable to help.
Rescue workers found the body of the pilot, who was alone on board.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter, belonging to a private company, called for help
only five minutes earlier, at 0856 GMT. Rega said another person
was killed and three injured when it came down in the Bernina
region. It is not yet clear if it crashed on Swiss or Italian
territory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
