<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Inspects Provinces in NE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
called on the nation to grasp opportunities to meet the challenges
brought by the world development trend and step up economic
development to ensure all-round achievements in China's
modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks during an inspection tour of
Heilongjiang and Jilin provinces in northeast China, which started
August 22 and concluded today.
</P>
<P>
During the week-long tour, Jiang Zemin visited cities,
factories, fields, high-tech companies, Sanjiang Plain, the Daqing
Oilfield in Heilongjiang and the No.1 Automobile Factory in Jilin.
</P>
<P>
He also listened to work reports by provincial leaders on local
social and economic development, urging them to work hard and
strengthen party building and construction of the legal system.
</P>
<P>
Jiang urged people in Heilongjiang and Jilin to implement all
tasks set by the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China
(CPC), work hard, make innovative progress, promote economic
growth, accelerate reforms of traditional industrial bases and
make new achievements.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with state farm workers in Heilongjiang, Jiang
said the great changes at the Great Northern Wilderness (in
northeast China) was led by the three generations of farm workers.
"You have made a big step forward in promoting agricultural
mechanization and narrowing the gap between urban districts and
rural areas. Construction of small towns has taken shape." Jiang
called on participants to work hard to achieve their objective of
farm mechanization around 2005.
</P>
<P>
While visiting the Daqing Oilfield and the First Automobile
Works, Jiang said, industrial regrouping and structural upgrading
should be guided by market needs. He urged people in the
industrial sector to speed up transformation of traditional
industry with new and high technology, turn out marketable and
technology-intensive products and build new aspects of industrial
growth.
</P>
<P>
Backbone enterprises will be formed in key sectors of the
national economy. Through enterprise merger and regrouping, the
country is to build a number of enterprise groups which are free
to handle their own intellectual property rights and perform well,
he said.
</P>
<P>
The president was accompanied by Vice Premier Wen Jiabao, also
a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China (
CPC) Central Committee and member of the secretariat; Zeng
Qinghong, alternate member of the Political Bureau of the CPC
Central Committee and member of the secretariat, as well as head
of Organization Department of the CPC Central Committee; and
Heilongjiang and Jilin provincial government officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
