<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Hands Over to U.S. Five Sets of MIA Remains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam Monday handed over to U.S.
representatives five sets of remains identified as belonging to
American servicemen missing in action (MIA) during the Vietnam war,
Vietnam News Agency (VNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The remains were found by the Vietnam-U.S. joint task force in
their joint 61st operation from June 26 to July 25 and by the
Vietnamese alone.
</P>
<P>
The remains have undergone primary forensic testing by
specialists of both sides for identification.
</P>
<P>
The hand-over, which was conducted by the Vietnam Office for
Seeking Missing Persons (VNOSMP) and the U.S. Joint Task Force-
Full Accounting (JTF-FA), was the 79th of its kind since 1973.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam has so far returned the remains of 772 MIA's to the
United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
