<HEADLINE> Beijing Holds First Int'l Fruits Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Over 300 fruit dealers from over
20 countries and regions brought their delicious fruits, and nuts
as well, to Beijing for the International Fruits Fair, which
started here today.
</P>
<P>
At the fair are more than 50 kinds of fruit including
grapefruits and grapes from the United States, Thai civet durian (
a kind of nut), Vietnamese litchis and longans, Malaysian pawpaws,
peaches and pears, Philippine mango, and Chinese chestnuts
produced in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Fair organizers said the two-day fair will help Beijing to
improve fruit quality, upgrade technology for growing and
processing fruit, and familiarize themselves with foreign
packaging designs, keep up with international fruit market
development.
</P>
<P>
There will be trade negotiations, meetings between Chinese and
overseas fruit growers, and visits to Beijing orchards. A website
has also been launched for businesspeople to do on-line business
transactions with some 1,500 tons of imported fruits to choose
from.
</P>
<P>
More overseas fruits have been on sale in Beijing in recent
years, and the city's sales volume for fruits last year reached 1.
486 million tons, and about two-thirds were imported from overseas
or other Chinese provinces.  
