<HEADLINE> Larg Wild Animal Park in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The construction of the
Hangzhou Wild Animal World started today in east China's Zhejiang
Province, east China.
</P>
<P>
The park, located in Fuyang, 15 kilometers from the Hangzhou
downtown area, is the largest of its kind in east China and covers
an area of 233 hectares. The park is the home to over 4,300
animals of some 160 species.
</P>
<P>
Investors said the park is to be open to the public when
finishing the first-stage of construction in May 2001. All the
animals will be in the open air and the whole project is expected
to cost 133 million yuan (about 15.96 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The park will be built into an ecological complex for animal
breeding, wildlife protection, popularization of science and
research activities. 
</P>
