<HEADLINE> HK's Exchange Fund Up in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The total assets of the
Exchange Fund of Hong Kong amounted to 982.8 billion HK dollars (
128 billion U.S. dollars) as at July 31, 2000, announced the Hong
Kong Monetary Authority (HKMA) Monday.
</P>
<P>
The figure is included in the Exchange Fund Abridged Balance
Sheet, which is released on a monthly basis together with the
Currency Board Account.
</P>
<P>
At the end of July 2000, the total assets of the Exchange Fund,
at 982.8 billion HK dollars, were 26.6 billion HK dollars (3.4
billion U.S. dollars) higher than at the end of June.
</P>
<P>
Both foreign currency assets and Hong Kong dollar assets
increased by 16.4 billion HK dollars (2.1 billion U.S. dollars)
and 10.2 billion HK dollars (1.3 billion U.S. dollars)
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The increase in foreign currency assets was primarily due to an
increase in the amount of repurchase agreements outstanding at the
end of the month, according to HKMA.
</P>
<P>
The increase in Hong Kong dollar assets reflected an increase
in the market value of Hong Kong equities that was partly offset
by a decrease in placements by other government funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
