<HEADLINE> India Slashes Long Distance Call Tariff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The Telecom Regulatory
Authority of India (TRAI) Monday announced a sharp cut in tariff
of up to 4.80 rupees (0.11 U.S. dollar) per minute for domestic
long distance calls and 12 rupees (0.27 dollar) for international
calls.
</P>
<P>
The new rates will be effective from October 1, 2000 and remain
valid till March 2002, TRAI said in a statement here.
</P>
<P>
The decrease in tariff rate is part of second phase of re-
balancing which was earlier scheduled from April this year, it
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
