<HEADLINE> Xodoin Festival Celebrated in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Tens of thousands of Tibetans,
clad in their holiday best, gathered at the Potala Palace in
central Lhasa today to celebrate the beginning of the annual
Xodoin Festival.
</P>
<P>
The Xodoin Festival, which is also called the Tibetan Opera
Festival, is held each year from the end of the sixth month to the
middle of the seventh month on the Tibetan calendar. Xodoin means
yogurt banquet.
</P>
<P>
Qiangba Punco, secretary of the Tibetan Autonomous Regional
Committee of the Communist Party of China, announced the opening
of the festival in both Tibetan and standard Chinese. Then
colorful balloons were set free, yaks danced while music played.
</P>
<P>
Losang Gyalcan, mayor of Lhasa, said the city tries to make
more friends and seek investment from all parts of the country by
holding economic and trade fairs during the festival.
</P>
<P>
Soinam Pazhu, an elder female Tibetan, recalled, the old rules
stipulate that people were not allowed to wear shoes while
watching a drama and women could neither style their hair nor
speak or laugh during the festival. "Nowadays, the Xodoin Festival
is one of the joyful events in Tibet," she said.
</P>
<P>
During the week-long festival, Lhasa, capital of Tibet, will
hold a variety of activities including Tibetan dramas and
performances, a fashion show, a lantern show, trade fair and a
horsemanship demonstration.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
