<HEADLINE> Beijing Holds Economic Forum on Modernization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The two-day Beijing Economic
Forum 2000 started today, focusing on how to realize modernization
in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
Fan Yuanmou, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of Beijing
Municipal People's Congress, said economists both at home and
abroad, well-known businessmen, representatives from various
industries and government officials gathered in the nation's
capital to make suggestions and recommendations for Beijing's
tenth five-year plan and the city's development strategy to 2010.
</P>
<P>
There were eight topics set today for seminars and they were:
means and policies for modernization, Zhongguancun IT area
development, Beijing's challenges and opportunities after China's
entry into the World Trade Organization, West China's development
and Beijing, real estate market prices and policies, non-public
economic development and south Beijing's reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
The forum is set as an annual activity, with scholars and
businessmen invited to discuss key issues in Beijing's economic
development. 
</P>
