<HEADLINE> State Councilor Meets Thai Vice-Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- State Councilor Luo Gan met with
visiting Vice-Foreign Minister Sukhumbhand Paribatra of Thailand
here today and exchanged views on drug trafficking and related
issues.
</P>
<P>
Luo said the drug issue concerns everyone. To solve drug
problems requires the support and cooperation of China and the
international community. However, international cooperation should
be conducted in accordance with the UN Charter, especially on the
basis of mutual respect and non-interference in each other's
internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
Luo briefly introduced China's stance and efforts on
eliminating drugs, stressing China and Thailand, as close
neighbors have been working hard to stamp out the problem and they
should work closely together in dealing with drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
Sukhumbhand said both Thailand and China are near the Golden
Triangle Area. For this reason, it is necessary that both
countries work closely together.
</P>
<P>
He appreciated China's efforts in eliminating drug, saying that
Thailand has a lot to learn from China in dealing with drugs.
</P>
