<HEADLINE> Chinese, Japanese FMs Discuss Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan said today that at present, Sino-Japanese relations have
generally maintained a good development momentum, and their
cooperation in many areas has yielded some results, thus enriching
the content of Sino-Japanese friendship and cooperation devoted to
peace and development.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks while meeting today with Japanese Foreign
Minister Yohei Kono, who arrived here earlier today for a four-day
official visit to China.
</P>
<P>
At the turn of the century, Tang said, it is imperative to
mobilize all the positive elements, and overcome and restrain
negative elements, so as to promote bilateral relations in a
stable manner.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji will pay an official
visit to Japan in October, which will be a major event in
bilateral relations at the turn of the century, adding that the
two countries should closely cooperate on and make full
preparations for the visit.
</P>
<P>
Agreeing with Tang's comments on Sino-Japanese relations, Kono
said that friendly relations between the two countries are the
main stream and general situation of bilateral relations, and Sino-
Japanese Joint Statement constitutes the foundation of such
relations, adding that the Japanese government stands firmly for
that.
</P>
<P>
He said that Japan attaches great importance to Chinese Premier
Zhu Rongji's upcoming visit to Japan, and is making serious
preparations, which he believes will promote the development of
bilateral relations. 
</P>
