<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 28 (Xinhua) - The Australian sharemarket
closed marginally lower Monday.
</P>
<P>
The All Ordinaries Index ended 3.6 points lower at 3,322.7
points while the S&AMP;P/ASX200 index lost 3.5 points to 3,363.9.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 444.02 million shares traded for 1.2
billion Australian dollars (687.6 U.S. million dollars). Falling
stocks outnumbered rising ones 790 to 657 while 549 were steady.
</P>
<P>
Banks were all lower as ANZ fell 7 Australian cents to 13.18
Australian dollars, Westpac dropped 8 cents to 12.87 Australian
dollars and Macquarie dipped 13 cents to 27.7 Australian dollars.
National Australia Bank was down 33 cents at 26.1 Australian
dollars while Commonwealth Bank lost 19 cents to 29.65 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Insurance giant AMP dropped 35.1 cents to 17.889 Australian
dollars and Telstra finished 9 cents higher at 6.81 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
News Corp finished 4.5 cents higher at 22.645 Australian
dollars while PBL fell 13.8 cents to 14.51 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the resources sector, Rio Tinto lost 56.3 cents to 27.95
Australian dollars. 
</P>
