<HEADLINE> Indonesia Sets Programs to Accelerate Economic Recovery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government on
Monday sets programs in a bid to accelerate the on-going economic
recovery process.
</P>
<P>
The programs include creating financial stability, increasing
the people's social welfare to strengthen political and social
stability, developing small and medium industries, increasing
farmers' welfare and productivity.
</P>
<P>
The programs made by an economic meeting will prioritize the
equity-based recovery instead of loan-based recovery, increase
exports, launch the value-creation privatization program, carry
out the economic decentralization and safeguard fiscal balancing,
optimize the using of natural resources as well as accelerate
corporate and banking restructuring programs.
</P>
<P>
The newly-appointed Coordinating Minister for Economic Affairs
Rizal Ramli said that the government will finalize the draft of
the programs by next Monday.
</P>
<P>
"The office of coordinating ministry for economic affairs has
instructed economic ministers to make the program successful by
setting the supporting programs, arranging action agenda and make
target of achievement," Ramli told a press conference on Monday
evening.
</P>
<P>
He also said that the country's currency of rupiah has regained
strength as it traded at the level of 8,200 per U.S. dollar on
Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
"It shows that negative perceptions (made by market) on the new
cabinet is baseless. I am optimistic that the rupiah will keep
strengthening as the above programs are launched," he added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Ramli also said that his side has asked economic
ministers to prepare themselves to conduct exchange of ideas with
the economic multilateral organizations such as the International
Monetary Fund (IMF), the World Bank (WB) and the Asian Development
Bank (ADB).
</P>
<P>
"The office of coordinating ministry for economic affairs is
optimistic that the cooperation between the government and the
economic multilateral institutions will bring benefit to all of us.
Both for the Indonesian government and the multilateral
organizations, the most important thing is (for) the benefit for
the Indonesian people," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
