<HEADLINE> Maize Prices to Remain Low in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Times of Zambia Monday quoted ACE general manager Hans Brammer
as saying here at the weekend that there are no sales taking place
on the commodity exchange, due to lack of money on the market to
boost the sale of the commodity.
</P>
<P>
The other factor to keep maize prices low is the fall in demand
for maize, staple food for the Zambians, he said.
</P>
<P>
The market is saturated with maize hence some farmers have
resorted to selling it at cheaper prices, according to the local
newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Brammer said other factors that have made maize buying
unattractive are the current high transportation costs, unstable
foreign exchange rate and rising inflation.
</P>
<P>
Brammer is however optimistic that after the just ended Zambia
National Farmers Union congress, modalities could be worked out to
boost the maize prices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
