<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Technology Exhibition Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 28 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition on technical
items for import and export opened today in this capital city of
south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Over 70 Chinese and overseas companies have brought to the
three-day exhibition their latest technologies for trading at the
three-day event, covering the information industry, machine
building, bio-medicines, new environmental protection materials
and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Guangzhou has introduced nearly 50,000
items of advanced technology and equipment from around the world
since 1979, at a cost of 13.3 billion U.S. dollars, for the
technological transformation of its key enterprises.
</P>
<P>
As a result, Guangzhou has exported more than one billion U.S.
dollars worth of technical items since 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
