<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank of China Has Business Building in Pudong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China (BOC) is
scheduled to move its Shanghai Branch to the Pudong New District
at the end of this year as construction of its business building,
the Zhongyin Mansion, was completed today.
</P>
<P>
The BOC, Shanghai Lujiazui Co. Group and the Bank of East Asia
Ltd. in Hong Kong have jointly invested some 200 million U.S.
dollars in the project.
</P>
<P>
The new building is 258 meters high and has 56 floors. Its
business hall, foreign exchange center and telephone-bank center
will provide convenient and efficient financial service to
customers, according to banking experts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
