<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Website Rated as Key Resource on Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The website of China's Legal
Daily -- www.legaldaily.com.cn, was recently listed as the fourth
among the key resources on law by Link2go, a US-based website
rating body.
</P>
<P>
Two other local websites and two overseas websites are also
among the five best known "key resources" on Chinese law.
</P>
<P>
Linksgo is a well-known international analyzer website
information.
</P>
<P>
A website that has been selected as a key resource means it is
one of the most frequently surfed on a subject. Less than one in a
thousand websites have the chance to become a key resource website.
</P>
<P>
The Legal Daily's website was opened on January 1, 1999, and
since then, it has been upgraded several times and has become a
showcase for the rest of the world to learn about the legal issues
in China.
</P>
<P>
In addition to using the paper's stories, the website also
publishes news collected by its own staff, including in-depth
reports on hot topics and major events. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
