<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ministry Circular on Student Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Education has
called on all universities and colleges to attach great importance
to the issue of granting student loans.
</P>
<P>
In a circular published today, the ministry urged higher
learning institutions to carry out specific guidelines recently
issued by the People's Bank of China, the Ministry of Education
and the Ministry of Finance.
</P>
<P>
The education loans for students from poor families is a major
step for implementing the government strategy of reinvigorating
the nation through science, technology and education. It also
helps improve the development of China's educational sector and
deepen the reform of the education system.
</P>
<P>
Specific departments and individuals should be appointed by
schools to coordinate student loans.
</P>
<P>
It also asks the colleges to assist banks that have been
selected to make the loans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
