<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Minister Urges to Fire Law-Breaking Medical Staff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- China's Minister of Health Zhang
Wenkang today urged local authorities and hospitals to curb
rampant malfeasances among medical workers and dismiss those who
have violated the law.
</P>
<P>
The minister made the call at a teleconference on improving the
style of work in the medical sector and promoting medical reform
in urban and rural areas.
</P>
<P>
If the malpractices are not stopped, the health and safety of
the people will be threatened and the general goal of medical
reform will not be realized, Zhang warned, who called for more
efforts to educate medical workers on professional ethics and law.
</P>
<P>
In recent months, a series of malpractices and illegal
activities by local hospitals have been exposed by the media.
</P>
<P>
In one instance, doctors at a hospital in Harbin, the
provincial capital of Heilongjiang, profiteered from patients by
making changes in medical records and forcing the patients to stay
on in the hospital for more days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
