<HEADLINE> Teleconference on Winter Recruitment Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- A national teleconference on the
recruitment held here today demanded localities to regard the
issue as a political task and exert efforts to mobilize
outstanding persons to join the army in winter.
</P>
<P>
Last winter's recruitment was well accomplished under the
leadership of the State Council and the Central Military
Commission and due to cooperation between the army and local
governments.
</P>
<P>
The meeting urged localities to study President Jiang Zemin's
important instructions on the army, to ensure the quality of the
recruits. Young people should be made more better aware of the
glory and obligation to join the army, it says.
</P>
<P>
Related regulations on recruitment must be strictly followed so
that the recruits can be politically and physically qualified,
have a good educational background, and have reached the right age
to be allowed to join the army.
</P>
<P>
Senior army officers and a group of central and local
government officials in charge of recruitment attended the
teleconference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
