<DOCNO> XIE20000828.0146 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Mixed on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed mixed on
Singapore Stock Market Monday with index heavyweight SingTel
sliding and banks stocks rising.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) ended 9.82 points
higher at 2,176.11 in quiet dealings.
</P>
<P>
The total volume contracted to 214.93 million units worth 368.
75 million Singapore dollars (214.39 million U.S. dollars).
Declining issues outstripped advancers by 194 to 107 with 202
counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Brierley topped the volume list as it registered a turnover of
31.24 million units. It was followed by SingTel which had 8.88
million shares done. MediaRing was the next with 8.13 million
counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
UOB became the biggest gainer of the day after a surge of 90
cents to close at 13.7 Singapore dollars. Datacrft went up 30
cents to finish at 8.3 U.S. dollars. OUB edged up 25 cents to end
at 8.6 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
PacCent and Venture led the descent of the day with a loss of
30 cents each to close at 22.8 and 22.7 Singapore dollars
respectively. SIA 200 shed 20 cents to finish at 16.9 Singapore
dollars. JurEng slid by 15 cents to end at 1.75 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers noted that the day's volume was sparse in the absence
of fresh leads and the market remained fragile.
</P>
<P>
They noted that index heavyweight SingTel fell on profit-taking
after days of gains, dragging down the STI.
</P>
<P>
Bank stocks were up on situational play and bargain hunting
after weak performances late last week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
