<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodia, Vietnam Sign Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The visiting Vietnamese
Deputy Prime Minister Nguyen Tandung Monday held talks here with
Cambodia's Deputy Prime Minister Sar Kheng and the two sides
signed three agreements.
</P>
<P>
The accords include one on scientific and technical cooperation
in agriculture, forestry and fisheries, one on health and the
other on the accounting, exhumation and repatriation of remains of
Vietnamese soldiers killed in action during the wartime in
Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
According to the local media, this is the first time for
Vietnam to request an agreement on accounting and repatriating the
remains of Vietnamese soldiers who were killed in Cambodia from
1979 to 1989.
</P>
<P>
Nguyen Tandung Monday separately met with Prime Minister Hun
Sen and President of the Senate Chea Sim.
</P>
<P>
Nguyen Tandung, who arrived here on August 27, is scheduled to
visit Angkor Wat, one of the four ancient Oriental wonders, on
Tuesday before returning home on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
