<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar ended
firmer Monday.
</P>
<P>
The currency ended at 57.32 U.S. cents, from 57.21 at the close
of local trading Friday.
</P>
<P>
During the session, the currency traded from an opening high of
57.44 U.S. cents down to a low of 57.28.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar lost 2 U.S. cents in two days last week
and analysts said it would not be able to bounce back to above the
60-cent mark this year.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year there was optimistic speculation that the
currency could come near 70 U.S. cents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
