<DOCNO> XIE20000828.0151 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank to Provide 62 Million Dollar Loan to India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government has
signed a 62 million U.S. dollar loan agreement with the World Bank
to reform the Indian telecommunications sector.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be used for the "Telecommunications Sector
Reforms Technical Assistance Project," to which the Indian
government will also contribute 10 million dollars, an official
release said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The telecom sector reform project is expected to bring a number
of benefits. The automation and modernization of spectrum
management will result in more efficient use of this scarce
resource, faster assignment of frequencies and more effective
monitoring of unauthorized operations, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
