<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Monday as investors awaited the
release of more corporate results by major companies this week.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index lost 2.87
points to 796.39, the all-share Emas Index shed 1.24 points to 198.
24, the Industrial Index dropped 25.17 points to 1,404.62 and the
Second Board Index fell 1.78 points to 204.03.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 487 to 120 while 156 counters were
unchanged and 234 counters untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's total turnover declined to 74.751 million shares
valued at 224.513 million ringgit (59.08 million U.S. dollars)from
85.925 million shares worth 316.978 million ringgit (83.41 million
dollars) last Friday. 
</P>
