<HEADLINE> Fire in Russian Central TV Tower Controlled: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The fire that broke out on Sunday
in the Ostankino television tower in Moscow was controlled at 12:
32 p.m.(0832 GMT) on Monday, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The fire is unlikely to spread lower than the 63-meters mark,
where firemen mounted nonflammable barriers last night, Interfax
cited head of the Moscow fire department Leonid Korotchik as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Nonetheless, firemen are pouring liquid into the cable shafts,
and a foam attack can be made anytime if needed, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
