<HEADLINE> China's First Nuclear Plant Begins to Issue Regular Environmental Monitoring Results </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 28 (Xinhua) -- China's first built nuclear
power plant has started to issue regular environmental monitoring
results.
</P>
<P>
According to the first report issued in mid-August by the
Qinshan nuclear power plant in east China's Zhejiang province,
environmental condition during the second season of this year is
normal.
</P>
<P>
Gu Peilong, an official in charge of the Zhejiang Environmental
Monitoring Station on Radiation, said the results will be
published in a local newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Ecological condition around the nuclear power plant will
probably be issued annually as well, according to Gu.
</P>
<P>
Five monitors have been erected within 2.5 kilometers of the
plant to carry out around-the-clock radiation monitoring. 
</P>
</TEXT>
