<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade in Beijing Booming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has registered a imports
and exports volume of 6.115 billion U.S. dollars in the first
seven months of this year, an increase of 38.2 percent over the
same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Exports rose 53.5 percent over the period. hitting 2.432
billion U.S. dollars, latest statistics from the Beijing Municipal
Customs showed.
</P>
<P>
Processing trade, valuing at 1.33 billion U.S. dollars, was
still the mainstay of export in Beijing. Exports by foreign-funded
enterprises accounted for 59.4 percent of general exports in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Machinery and electrical appliances were among the leading
imported items of Beijing during the first seven months. The
imports value registered an increase of 30.5 percent in the period
to reach 2.94 billion U.S. dollars, making up 79.7 percent of
Beijing's overall imports value.
</P>
<P>
Imports by foreign-funded enterprises reached 2.62 billion U.S.
dollars in the seven months, accounting for 71.2 percent of the
total imports volume in Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
