<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Bourse Invites 50 Specialists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Shenzhen Securities Exchange
announced today that the stock market would invite 50 accountants,
lawyers and computer specialists.
</P>
<P>
The move is designed to step up supervision and management over
the stock market and to promote a healthy development of the
market.
</P>
<P>
The list of recruitment will consist of 30 accountants, 10
lawyers and 10 computer experts. Candidates' age is restricted
below 30 years of old, but for those with senior professional
titles the age restriction will be under 35 years of age.
</P>
<P>
Candidates with experience studying or working overseas will be
preferred.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen Securities Exchange is one of China's only two stock
bourses. The other one is based in Shanghai. More than 500
businesses have listed their shares, with a combined market value
of two trillion yuan on the Shenzhen Securities Exchange. 
</P>
