<HEADLINE> Chinese Treasuries Stable on Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese treasuries stayed stable
as the stock market kept climbing towards the historical high set
last Monday and market confidence on stocks weakened as the stock
indices came higher and higher.
</P>
<P>
Transaction value on treasuries totaled 1.90 billion yuan, 627
million yuan more than that on last Friday, according to Homeway,
China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The new floating-rate 010004, whose coupon rate is 2.87 percent
this year, leapt 0.23 percent to 104.81 yuan, pressing the yield
down 0.02 percentage points to 2.37 percent.
</P>
<P>
009908 edged down 0.05 percent to end at 102.97 yuan,
accompanied by a 0.01 percentage point gain in the yield at 3.31
percent.
</P>
<P>
All the other bonds just hovered at the current prices
including Bond 009905, the most active performer with the biggest
trading volume of 752 million yuan among current bonds.
</P>
<P>
Trading value of three-day, seven-day, 14-day and 28-day
repurchasing transactions contracted to 1.52 billion yuan, down 1.
50 billion from the previous trading day. However, most of the
repurchasing interest rates witnessed tame rises. The interest
rate of the three-day repurchasing agreement recovered to 3.3
percent, from 0.64 percent on last Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
