<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Stock Market Up Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen Composite Index
closed up 3.55 points or 0.56 percent to its intraday high of 639.
84 points on Monday, while the sub-index finished at 4,957.57
points, up 6.82 points or 0.14 percent from the last close.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 12.65 billion yuan (1.52 billion US dollars),
which was 8.12 percent more than Friday's.
</P>
<P>
A news report relating to some positive comments on China's
stock market made by Zhou Xiaochuan, chairman of the China
Securities Regulatory Commission (CSRC), proved to be a boost to
the market. Zhou urged to speed up the preparation for the
establishment of the second board market, to cultivate
institutional investors with greater efforts, and to push forward
online securities trading.
</P>
<P>
After opening higher on a dynamic note, and hovering in a tight
trading range for most of the day, the Shenzhen stock market
managed to pace its upward move in the late day, boosted by
increased optimism on China's stock market, according to Homeway,
China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen Huafa Electronics Co., Ltd., the top gainer, rose 10.
01 percent to its price ceiling at 18.69 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Lhasa Brewery Co., Ltd., the biggest loser, was hit by profit-
taking, losing 10.01 percent to touch its price floor at 17.25
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Analysts note that much of bullish momentum is evident and will
lift the market to new highs as it has fast grip on the positive
ground for the current being.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000828.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen B-share Market Down at Monday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen B-share index shed
2.55 points, or 2.02 percent, to end at 123.95 points on Monday,
posting its fifth declines in a row.
</P>
<P>
Turnover continued to shrink, reaching 99.50 million HK dollars
(104.99 million yuan), which was 41.83 percent less than Friday's
total.
</P>
<P>
Opening lower on a weak note, the market failed to revive from
its recent tumble for an extreme lack of bullish momentum in
morning activity. Follow through moves on the selling side
developed with lackluster volume, making any rally attempts in the
afternoon session futile in the end, according to Homeway, China's
leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Decling shares outpaced advancing issues by 41 to 12, with
three unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Huafa Elect rose 6.46 percent to 2.80 HK dollars, while ST
Tellus added 2.45 percent to 2.09 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
Huaxin lost 4.41 percnet to 2.60 HK dollars, while Sez Real
Estate fell 4.17 percent to 2.30 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
The thought that the index has become a bit overextended
technically and that it is poised to pull back spells no upward
movement is expected to take place very soon, market analysts said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
