<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Fund Market Stable on Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- On Monday, China's securities
investment fund market moved steadily, showing a similar
performance compared with last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The 22 discounted funds continued to follow the price level
after last Thursday's rally. Five rising funds, which were all
discounted funds, were Fund Tianyuan, Fund Yuyuan, Fund Kaiyuan,
Fund Taihe that had released its interim report, and Fund Yuyang
that began its strong movement from last Friday, according to
Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory
company.
</P>
<P>
Three funds that dropped more than one percent were Fund
Tongzhi, Fund Handing, and Fund Jinding down 1.23 percent, 1.19
percent and 1.15 percent.
</P>
<P>
There was no interim report release today, which was sort of
out of market expectation. This may be a reason for the market to
move steadily today.
</P>
<P>
Last week, as the composite indexes on the two stock markets
declined within a certain range, down 0.17 percent and 0.41
percent on a weekly basis. Among the 30 funds, only eight funds
realized premiums for their net assets values, up from 0.56
percent to 0.007 percent. In particular, Fund Kaiyuan and Fund
Tongzhi dropped more than 0.5 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
