<HEADLINE> Li Peng Leaves for UN Meeting and Five-Nation Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the
Standing Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC),
left Beijing for New York today for the Conference of Presiding
Officers of National Parliaments to be held at the United Nations
headquarters.
</P>
<P>
Li will deliver a speech at the August 30 opening ceremony of
the conference expounding on China's stance on international
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He will also meet with UN Secretary-General, leaders of the
Inter-Parliamentary Union and parliament leaders from countries
during the conference. It is expected that Some 150 major leaders
of parliaments from countries across the world will attend the
conference.
</P>
<P>
After the conference from August 30 to September 1, Li will
visit Iceland, Lithuania, Estonia, Latvia and Russia starting from
September 2.
</P>
<P>
During Li's visit to the five nations, Li will meet with
parliament and government leaders and people from all walks of
life to deepen mutual understanding and trust and stimulate
healthy and steady relations with these countries.
</P>
<P>
Li's entourage includes his wife Zhu Lin, Secretary General He
Chunlin of the NPC Standing Committee, members of the NPC Standing
Committee Wang Weicheng, Li Boyong, Fan Jingyi, Shi Yuxiao, and
other senior officials.
</P>
<P>
Among those seeing Li off at the Great Hall of the People this
afternoon were Vice-Chairman Tian Jiyun of the NPC Standing
Committee, State Councilor Luo Gan, Vice-Chairman Tomur Dawamat of
the NPC Standing Committee, and other senior officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
