<HEADLINE> Manila Stocks End Higher on Hostages' Release </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Share prices at the Philippine
Stock Exchange closed higher Monday, boosted by the release of
five hostages in the southern Philippine province of Sulu.
</P>
<P>
The 30-company Phisix, the market's main index, added 11.72
points to close at 1,505.2.
</P>
<P>
The broader all-shares index also went 12.49 points higher to
673.89.
</P>
