the
financial index which lost 3.56 points to close at 539.99.
</P>
<P>
Some analysts said investors positioned in highly capitalized
issues as they saw some positive development in the months-long
hostage crisis in Sulu.
</P>
<P>
"The release of the hostages lifted market sentiment," said
Jose Vistan, a local market analyst.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, five hostages were freed by the Abu Sayyaf,followed
by the release of one more hostage, a South African male,on Monday.
But one Filipino and six more foreigners are still in the hands of
the group. 
