</P>
<P>
MADRID -- A peace accord with Israel is still possible despite
the collapse of the Camp David summit, Spanish and Palestinian
leaders said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat, during a private
meeting with Spanish Prime Minister Maria Aznar, reaffirmed the
Palestinian positions on Jerusalem and other key issues such as
the return of refugees and water rights. Aznar said Spain and
other European Union members will acknowledge a Palestinian state
whether Arafat would declare its establishment on September 13 as
originally planned or delay the announcement. (Spain-Arafat)
</P>
