<HEADLINE> Two Russian Army Deserters Found Dead in Central Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Two Russian sergeants who escaped
from their unit in the Moscow region were found dead on Sunday
evening near the city of Ivanovo, 260 kilometers east of Moscow,
Russian media reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Their bodies with gunshot wounds were discovered in a garage
near Ivanovo at 8:30 p.m. (1630 GMT). Investigators believe that
they committed suicide, said the Interfax news agency.
</P>
<P>
The two sergeants, Alexander Svyatkin and Maxim Uzhintsev, left
an Interior Ministry unit in Lynyovo, Solnechnogorsk district, at
about 5 a.m. (0100 GMT) Sunday morning with two assault rifles and
10 magazines of ammunition, the Itar-Tass news agency quoted an
Interior Ministry officer as saying Monday.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary investigation indicated that the two servicemen
committed suicide. Field investigation groups are ascertaining all
the circumstances of the incident, said the officer.
</P>
<P>
According to information from law enforcement agencies,
Svyatkin opened the firearms room and took the Kalashnikov rifles
and ammunition when on duty in his company. Together with his
buddy, Uzhentsev, the fugitives deserted the unit upon donning
police uniform, Tass said.
</P>
<P>
It was disclosed that Svyatkin was a native of Ivanovo.
Therefore, operatives did not rule it out that the fugitives were
heading for that city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
