<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
closed higher here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 36 points higher at 2,093 with a healthy
turnover of 192.8 million NZ dollars (84 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
New Zealand's largest listed company Telecom, which makes up
about a third of the stock market, rose 38 cents to 682 cents,
market No. 2 stock Carter Holt Harvey 2 cents to 180 cents and
industrial giant Fletcher Energy 33 cents to 835 cents.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand's largest brewer Lion Nathan gained 3 cents to 473
cents,pay television network Sky TV 2 to 380 cents and Fletcher
Forests 1 to 89 cents.
</P>
<P>
Dual-listed insurer AMP fell 30 cents to 2,350 cents and
Natural Gas Corporation 2 to 156 cents.
</P>
<P>
Fletcher Building, discount retailer the Warehouse and
Australia-New Zealand Bank all closed unchanged at 225, 570 and 1,
740 cents respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
