<HEADLINE> Tropical Storm Kills 7 in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Depression Kaemi, a tropical
storm, has claimed seven lives and caused more than 254 million
baht (6 million U.S. dollars) in damages when it swept through 19
provinces in northeastern Thailand last week, according to a
government report Monday.
</P>
<P>
The report, released here by the Interior Ministry said after
the storm traversed the country from August 24 to 27, now flooding
still persists in 12 of the 19 affected provinces.
</P>
<P>
In the worst-hit province of Si Sa Ket, 571 kilometers
northeast of Bangkok, the storm has damaged 233 roads, 142,000
hectares of farmland and over a thousand houses. 415,664 residents
there were evacuated, but are still unable to return their homes,
it said.
</P>
<P>
The report also warned that a possible new storm may come to
the country in a few days. 
</P>
