<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Rule to Boost Used-Car Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The pending modification of the
country's automobile exhaust regulations is expected to be a
strong incentive to private sedan market.
</P>
<P>
The new rule will result in more dynamic market, especially in
the second-hand car sales, according to the vehicle supervision
division under the Municipal Public Security Bureau quoted by
today's "China Daily".
</P>
<P>
The modification, which is expected to be introduced by the end
of this year, may allow automobiles nationwide to keep running
past the age of ten.
</P>
<P>
Under the current system, effective since 1994, automobiles
have to be taken out of service after ten years of usage, despite
their condition.
</P>
<P>
"Sometimes it is not reasonable to discard the autos in spite
that they are still in good conditions, especially as more sedans
are becoming private possessions," said Chen Weiqiang, vehicle
administration official under the division.
</P>
<P>
The move will provoke consumers' long-suppressed eagerness to
buy private sedans, analysts said. Usually private car owners are
unwilling to get rid of a high-priced car after certain years of
service without considering its condition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
