<HEADLINE> Indonesian Firm Breaks Hair-Washing Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 28 (Xinhua) -- A shampoo producer broke a world
record for the number of heads washed in a day after its
shampooers and stylists washed 4,887 heads on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The record was broken at the National Monument park in Central
Jakarta. The event started from the morning hours and lasted until
about 2:00 p.m., the Jakarta Post daily reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The organizer, PT Procter and Gamble Indonesia, a manufacturer
of consumer goods, reportedly decided to halt the free shampooing
event as the number of volunteers wanting their hair washed was
increasing.
</P>
<P>
The company earlier expected to surpass 5,000 heads by 5:00 p.m.
</P>
<P>
But the total exceeded Vietnam's record of 4,100, Malaysia's 1,
068 and Singapore's 948.
</P>
<P>
All the heads washed in the event were closely monitored by
representatives from the Indonesian Museum of Record (MURI). Some
200 shampooers and 504 stylists took part in the event.
</P>
<P>
The event raised funds totaling 17.1 million rupiah (2,060 U.S.
dollars) to be donated in the form of mini libraries and books to
four schools for the needy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
