<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Province Reports Big Rise in Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province
reported a year-on-year 48 percent rise in exports to 13.8 billion
US dollars from January to July this year.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of the year, local exports have kept
growing by an average of 47 percent every month, a consecutive big
rise which has not been seen in the past six years.
</P>
<P>
Local overseas-funded enterprises did 7.57 billion US dollars
in exports during the January-July period, a rise of 50 percent on
a yearly basis, with the exports by private enterprises being 10
times the 1999 figure to 47 million US dollars in the seven months.
</P>
<P>
Exports of electron-machinery rose 58 percent to 6.25 billion US
dollars, with the volume of high-tech items growing by 60 percent
to 2.7 billion US dollars, and textiles went up 44 percent, 3.9
billion US dollars. 
</P>
