<HEADLINE> Autumn Locusts Invade East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, August 28 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong province has
yet to get a break in its battle against summer locusts and now
autumn locusts are swarming in.
</P>
<P>
So far, 213,000 hectares of land has been infested with a
density of two locusts per square meter.
</P>
<P>
Experts explained that the infestation of summer locusts has
helped a large number of dormant autumn locusts become active.
</P>
<P>
The area of land plagued by autumn locusts could reach 330,000
hectares, they warned. 
</P>
