<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Employs New Fresh-Keeping Technique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 28 (Xinhua) -- A new technique, developed by a
local scientist, will enable flowers and fruit to stay fresh for
as long as a month, almost 10 times longer than the traditional
technique does.
</P>
<P>
Using a vacuum cooling device that keeps the fruit fresh,
developed by a scientist with the Shanghai Jiaotong University,
the dehydration of agricultural products will be avoided and
nutrients will be preserved.
</P>
<P>
Traditional techniques to keep fruits and flowers fresh is
costly, and at the same time easily deforms the edible
agricultural products and changes their taste.
</P>
<P>
The device, however, costs only about one-tenth of the price
for the same abroad.
</P>
<P>
Experts pointed out that the flexibility and convenience in
handling the device makes it easy to be promoted.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Xianlu Vacuum Preservation Equipment Co. Ltd. has
already started to manufacture the equipment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
