<HEADLINE> Balkan Culture Ministers Sign Memorandum Over Olympic Flame </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The Culture Ministers of the
Balkan region Sunday signed a memorandum calling for the Athens
2004 Olympic Games flame passage through the neighboring Balkan
countries.
</P>
<P>
The memorandum was signed by the ministers of culture and
athletics of Albania, Bulgaria, Cyprus, Macedonia and Greece while
they were meeting in Florina, northern Greece within the framework
of the Prespes 2000 festival.
</P>
<P>
Greek Culture Minister Theodoros Pangalos said that this marked
a significant moment for the region's peoples, those who fervently
wish for peace and cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
