<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. African Central Bank Governor Robbed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 27 (Xinhua) -- South African Reserve Bank
governor Tito Mboweni was robbed at an Oaklands garage in
Johannesburg Sunday afternoon, the South African Press Association
reported.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Johannesburg police inspector Amanda Roestoff
as saying that four armed men got away with Mboweni's cellphone
and items from six other customers.
</P>
<P>
The robbers entered a shop at the Caltex garage around 5:30 p.m.
local time and ordered four of the customers and a 29-year-old
security guard to lie on the ground, the inspector said.
</P>
<P>
She said Mboweni and two Swaziland citizens were ordered to
put their hands in the air.
</P>
<P>
The robbers stole Mboweni's Nokia cellphone, a 9 mm pistol
from Swaziland national Rickie Rennie and a cellphone from the
other Swaziland citizen, she said.
</P>
<P>
The robbers then ordered the guard to open a safe but he was
not able to do so because he did not have the keys, she added.
</P>
<P>
She said the men then stole jewelry from a 28-year-old cashier
and took an unknown amount of money from the till.
</P>
<P>
A gold chain and watch was also stolen from the owner of the
shop, she said.
</P>
<P>
The robbers then ran away, Roestoff said, adding that no shots
were fired and nobody was injured.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, despite the government's mounting
crackdown on crimes, robbery is still rampant in South Africa.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
