<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angolan President: Peace to Whom Wants It, War to Whom Wants It </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 27 (Xinhua)- - Angolan President Jos Eduardo dos
Santos said over the weekend that the lesson taken from the
Angolan peace process is that "we ought to offer peace to whom
wants peace, and war to whom wants war."
</P>
<P>
"No one can become stronger than the will of the people," he
said when opening the third military games of the Angolan Armed
Forces in Cabinda, capital of Cabinda Province, the official news
agency Angop reported.
</P>
<P>
According to Santos, it is a united, free people that should
determine their destiny and choose their government.
</P>
<P>
As long as the people cannot elect another government because
of the current circumstances, "our mission is to unite all the
people under the government of unity and national reconciliation,
forgetting about the time of divisions, and creating a moment of
union of all Angolans for national reconciliation and
reconstruction," he said.
</P>
<P>
That is the only way the government, in its turn, can create
the conditions for the building of an increasingly just, more
prosperous and more fraternal society, the president said.
</P>
<P>
Santos expressed satisfaction at the great victories that the
army and police forces have scored at battlefield.
</P>
<P>
As for the military games, the president said, they are a
testimony of the attention the army leaders do dedicate to a
multilateral development of their personnel and the creation of an
environment of healthy interaction and solidarity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
