<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UAE Congratulates Somalia Over First Elected President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates (UAE)
Monday expressed satisfaction over the outcome of the Somali
reconciliation conference which ended up by appointing Abdiqasim
Salad Hassan as the country's first elected president since 1991.
</P>
<P>
The UAE will continue its support for the solidarity with
Somalia and calls on the international community to support this
African country to pass this transitional period, an official
source at UAE Foreign Ministry told the official WAM news agency on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
He also called on all Somali parties to support the new
president and to work for the success of the experience.
</P>
<P>
The source expressed appreciations to Djibouti for hosting the
reconciliation conference.
</P>
<P>
Somalia has been divided since 1991 when former President
Mohamed Siad Barre was toppled.
</P>
<P>
Some 460 Somali representatives kicked off in May the country's
national reconciliation conference in Djibouti based on a
Djiboutian proposal. The conference established a 245-member
transition parliament on August 13, which elected Abdiqasim Salad
Hassan the Somali president. Both the parliament and the president
are the first in Somalia in a decade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
