<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000 GMT, August 28 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Five mortar shells hit an area surrounding the
deserted garrison of Heshmatieh in Tehran early Monday, but no
casualties or property damage were reported.
</P>
<P>
No one has claimed responsibility for the attacks. But the Iraq-
based opposition Mujahedeen Khalq Organization (MKO) were behind a
number of similar attacks before. (Iran-Shell-Garrison)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- The Turkish Cypriots have so far ignored pleas from
the U.N. to lift the unilateral restrictions on the movement of the
U.N. Peacekeeping Force in Cyprus (UNFICYP), said an U.N. envoy
here Monday.
</P>
<P>
After a meeting with Cyprus President Glafcos Clerides, U.N.
special representative in Cyprus Zbigniew Wlosowicz said that the
U.N. will draw its conclusion on the issue after evaluating all the
facts. (Cyprus-UN Envoy-UNFICYP)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkey attaches "vital" importance to the Middle East
peace process and "is ready to do its best" to contribute to it,
Turkish Prime Minister Bulent Ecevit said here onMonday.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark at a joint news conference following his
talks with Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak, who arrived in the
Turkish capital Ankara Monday for a brief working visit.
</P>
<P>
Barak said that Israel "is grateful" for Turkey's efforts and
initiatives within the framework of Mideast peace process, and will
take steps to further improve bilateral relations. (Turkey-Israel-
Barak)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Some Iraqi National Assembly (parliament) members
have proposed ways to ease the severe water shortage caused by
drought, a report reaching here said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Tariq Abed Lafta, head of the People's Affairs Committee in the
National Assembly, said that the legislators have suggested to cut
the water supply to garages and ice-making factories to save water.
</P>
<P>
Acute lack of water equipment has worsened the water shortage
problem, Lafta said, adding that Iraq is in urgent need of a large
number of generators to produce enough electricity to pump water to
areas lack of water. (Iraq-Drought) 
</P>
</TEXT>
