<HEADLINE> First Colombian Woman to Be Extradited to U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Colombia will extradite a woman
for the first time to the United States under charges of drug
trafficking, said the National Police.
</P>
<P>
Ivone Maria Scaff de Saldarriaga, who was captured along with
Gustavo Gomez Maya, is allegedly responsible for sending 65 tons
of cocaine to the United States.
</P>
<P>
General Luis Ernesto Guillibert, Director of the National
Police, said the operation was carried out in Venezuela, the
Caribbean islands and Colombia, with the participation of the
authorities of these countries and the collaboration of the United
States Drug Enforcement Agency (DEA), the Federal Bureau of
Investigation (FBI) and the Central Intelligence Agency (CIA).
</P>
<P>
The official said the seizure is the result of the intelligence
work of Colombian police officers supported by the DEA. But he did
not say anything on the details of the extradition.
</P>
<P>
He said that through satellite tracking, it was possible to
discover the net that operated from Colombia, with connections to
Europe and the United States.
</P>
<P>
Washington also announced the night before that the net had
been destroyed after a two-year international operation during
which 43 people were arrested. 
</P>
</TEXT>
