<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Not Ready to Implement SADC Trade Protocol: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 29 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe will not be able to meet
the Friday deadline for the implementation of the Southern African
Development Community (SADC) Free Trade Protocol, the country's
Industry and International Trade Minister Nkosana Moyo said on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Moyo made the remarks during the opening of the two-day
Confederation of Zimbabwe Industries conference on the SADC Trade
Protocol, the Common Market for Eastern and Southern Africa, the
World Trade Organization, and African, Caribbean and Pacific/
European Union Relations.
</P>
<P>
"We won't be able to meet the September 1, 2000 deadline," Moyo
said, explaining that "the protocol allows for entry at different
times and Zimbabwe will follow on the heels of the Southern
African Customs Union (SACU)."
</P>
<P>
SACU members -- Botswana, Lesotho, Namibia, South Africa and
Swaziland -- which have been trading on terms similar to the SADC
Free Trade Protocol for years, are more prepared to transform
their trade into a regional scale but the other nine SADC members,
Zimbabwe included, still have to organize themselves.
</P>
<P>
Actually, the SADC heads have agreed to split their countries
into the developed, developing and least developed categories for
tariff reduction purposes.
</P>
<P>
Developed countries are SACU members while the developing are
Mauritius and Zimbabwe and the last group comprises Malawi,
Mozambique, Tanzania and Zambia. The other three member countries,
namely Angola, the Democratic Republic of the Congo and Seychelles,
have not been included in these categories.
</P>
<P>
Countries in SACU will reduce the bulk of tariffs in the early
part of the eight-year free trade trial period while those in the
second category will reduce in the middle and the last group in
the last part of the period.
</P>
<P>
Moyo said Zimbabwe still needs to organize its administrative
capacity before depositing its instruments but he could not give
dates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000828.0291 </DOCNO>
