<HEADLINE> Angolan Government Offers Reconciliation to Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 29 (Xinhua) -- Angolan President Jose Eduardo
dos Santos has reiterated that his government welcomes all those
who drop guns, accept democracy and want to contribute to the
reconstruction of the country, the official news agency Angop
said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The president made this statement after a reception to
celebrate his 58th birthday on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Angola has space for all, the country belongs to all Angolans
and not only to a few, so it is useless to make war," said the
Angolan head of state.
</P>
<P>
The president added that what is necessary is that the people
give up arms, accept democracy and the free debate of ideas,
respect the difference of opinions and contribute to the national
reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
President dos Santos also reminded that during the campaign for
the general elections in 1992, he offered reconciliation with
Jonas Savimbi, leader of the UNITA rebel movement. But Savimbi
refused to accept the result of the elections and restarted the
civil war. 
</P>
</TEXT>
