<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Introduce Open Prison System for Women </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 29 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe Prison Services will
in the near future introduce the open prison system for women,
following the success of the one for men, The Herald reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Chief Prison Officer Charity Gezi told the newspaper on Monday
that the open prison system, which is still on trial in the
country, will be a success.
</P>
<P>
Currently there is only one open prison - Connemara in Kwekwe,
with about 110 inmates.
</P>
<P>
She said, "The open prison would be an ideal place for the
women with children as they will no longer be confined like in the
other prisons."
</P>
<P>
She added that the idea behind the open prison system was to
reintegrate the prisoners into society and it also reduced the
transmission of airborne diseases in closed prisons.
</P>
<P>
Inmates in open prisons enjoy outdoor recreational facilities,
have regular communication with outsiders and can also go back
home when the need arises.
</P>
<P>
"So far no prisoner has never returned from weekend visits and
if this trend continues then we can see more open prisons in the
country," she said.
</P>
<P>
She also said that inmates admitted into the open prison are
those with lighter crimes and sentenced to less than three years
in jail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
