<HEADLINE> Deutsch Telekom Announces New Purchase in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Powertel will be taken over for the time being by VoiceStream,
the mobile phone server the Deutsch Telekom bought one month ago.
If the U.S. authorities approve the purchases, the two will be
merged into one daughter company of DT.
</P>
<P>
VoiceStream and Powertel have 3 million customers and with
business licenses in almost all U.S. states, will be able to
establish a mobile phone net covering 245 potential users.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the two companies currently use GSM-standard,
compatible to the technology of Deutsch Telekom, which will pay
both purchases by share-swapping.
</P>
<P>
About one third of the U.S. senators have expressed their
opposition to DT's purchase of VoiceStream on the ground that the
German government has a majority share in the telecommunication
company. The German media dismissed the charge as U.S.
protectionist backlash. 
</P>
</TEXT>
