<HEADLINE> Two Killed in Arkansas Campus Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 28 (Xinhua) -- A student killed a professor
at the University of Arkansas before taking his own life Monday,
the first day of the fall semester, university officials said.
</P>
<P>
"We believe the two persons killed are a faculty member and a
graduate student, but that remains to be confirmed," Chancellor
John White said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
A local television station identified the dead faculty member
as English professor John Locke.
</P>
<P>
The unnamed graduate student entered Kimpel Hall, which houses
the English, journalism and foreign language departments, around
noon and shot the professor in an office.
</P>
<P>
Two university police officers rushed to Kimpel Hall after a
911 call.
</P>
<P>
Students and faculty were evacuated from the building after the
shooting, and classes there and in an adjacent building were
canceled.  
</P>
</TEXT>
