<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Rise on Market Confidence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks rose broadly
Monday as investors showed confidence in the market direction in
an improved interest rate environment.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 60.21 at 11,252.84
points, extending a rally which began a week ago. The blue chip
index rose as much as 120 points earlier in the trading.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also higher. The technology heavy
Nasdaq composite index rose 27.91 at 4,070.59 points and the
Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was up 7.64 at 1,514.09 points.
</P>
<P>
Stocks rose as investors have built confidence in the future
direction of the market since the Federal Reserve decided last
Tuesday to leave interest rates unchanged but held the door open
to possible action if a threat to inflation rises. A majority of
analysts believed that the central bank would not raise rates
further before the presidential election in November.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Reserve has raised rates six times since last
summer in an effort to cool off the U.S. economy and prevent
inflation from rising. A series of reports showed recently that
the economy is slowing and inflation remains tame.
</P>
<P>
Financial stocks rose across the board today, leading the Dow's
advance. Among them were J.P. Morgan and Citigroup. IBM also rose,
helping to push the blue chip index higher.
</P>
<P>
In the tech sector, Intel, Cisco Systems and Dell computer were
up, driving the Nasdaq index higher. Internet stocks have moved
back into the spotlight.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 2.73 at 675.26 and the American Stock
Exchange index was up 0.16 at 934.97. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies rose 1.37 at 526.48.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by an 8-to-7 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,470 down, 1,373 up and 526
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 722.92 million shares from 670.68
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
